-- IMF's Rato says dollar undervalued: report
-- 
-- Mon Oct 8, 2007 1:44am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/08/us-markets-dollar-rato-idUSMDT00444220071008

 

 MADRID  (Reuters) - The U.S. dollar is currently undervalued and this could cause volatility in the financial markets, International Monetary Fund Managing Director Rodrigo Rato said on Monday in an interview published by newspaper Expansion. 

 "The truth is that the dollar is undervalued," Rato said. "Its low value could cause market volatility."